Welcome

   Untitled1

Registration now open: Regonline BAAL 2016

   The BAAL 2016 programme is now available: Programme

   The 49th Annual Meeting of the British Association for Applied
   Linguistics will be hosted by Anglia Ruskin University in Cambridge on
   1–3 September 2016.

Keynote Speakers

   Ingrid Piller (Macquarie University, Sydney, Australia)

   Devyani Sharma (Queen Mary University of London, UK)

   Jean-Marc Dewaele (Birkbeck, University of London, UK)

   S. Pit Corder Lecture:

   Jan Hulstijn (University of Amsterdam, the Netherlands)

   Scholarship and prize winners:

   Congratulations to the winners of our prizes and scholarships at BAAL
   2016

   2016 Richard Pemberton Prize, Best Postgraduate Paper:
   Sally Zacharias; University of Nottingham: “Knowledge about language
   from a Cognitive Linguistics perspective: What content teachers might
   want to know”

   2016 Best Poster Prize:
   Kazutake Kita; Tokyo University of Science: “A historical keyword
   analysis into Applied Linguistics: A response to the special issue”

   Student/Early Career Researcher Scholarship:
   Yingna Wang, University of South Australia;
   Pierre-Luc Paquet, Universidad de Alicante;
   Disha Maheshwari, University of Warwick and University of Delhi Simona;
   Floare Bora, University of Essex

   Chris Brumfit:
   Ioanna Charalambous, King’s College London


